      • convertGlobToRegex

        public static String convertGlobToRegex(String pattern)
        Converts a standard POSIX Shell globbing pattern into a regular expression pattern. The result can be used with the standard java.util.regex API to recognize strings which match the glob pattern.

        See also, the POSIX Shell language: http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/utilities/xcu_chap02.html#tag_02_13_01

        See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1247772/is-there-an-equivalent-of-java-util-regex-for-glob-type-patterns

        Parameters:
        pattern - A glob pattern.
        Returns:
        A regex pattern to recognize the given glob pattern.

      • compareVersions

        public static int compareVersions(String version1,
                                  String version2)
        Compares two version strings. Only numeric versions are supported
        Parameters:
        version1 - the first version
        version2 - the second version
        Returns:
        -1 if version1 is is less than version. 1 if version2 is less than version1. 0 if equal
